void Matrix::AdjustVector (  int  type,
int  remainO,
int  from,
int  to
) 
 

PUBLIC: ADJUSTVECTOR.

If remainO is -1, sets each element of the vector in the range specified by from and to to 0. If remainO is 0, sets the vector element specified by type to 0. Otherwise, decreases the vector element specified by type by 1/(remain0 + 1) for each element in the matrix line specified by type that is greater than 0. Finally, normalizes the vector element range specified by from and to.

Normalize. Takes a two-dimenssional array of doubles, divides each element by the sum of all elements, and adds the value to the preceding value (sum of values) so that the last element is always 1.

void Matrix::TrimMatrix (  int  type,
float  density,
int  remainO,
int  durLoc
) 
 

TRIMMATRIX. Reads in individual arrays, builds another array(s) and multiplies it/them with the first set in order to obtain a weighted mean. Resulting matrix is normalized/scaled. **This function is used only for the duration matrix and performs similar tasks as the BuildMatrix function used only for the type/attacks matrix.**
